# STT-Nova2 Project Rules for Cursor AI

## Project Context
This is a Speech-to-Text service with FastAPI backend, Telegram bot integration, and AI summarization capabilities.

## Code Quality Standards

### Formatting & Style
- Use Black for code formatting (line length 88)
- Use isort for import sorting with Black profile
- Use flake8 for linting (max line length 88)
- Always use type hints for function parameters and return values
- Use snake_case for variables and functions, UPPER_CASE for constants

### Code Structure
- Keep functions small and focused (max 20 lines)
- Use descriptive names for functions, classes, and variables
- Write Google-style docstrings for all functions and classes
- Use async/await for I/O operations

### Testing Requirements
- Write unit tests using pytest for all new code
- Use descriptive test function names starting with `test_`
- Mock external dependencies (Deepgram, Gemini, Telegram)
- Maintain minimum 80% test coverage
- Test error handling scenarios and edge cases

### Security Standards
- Never commit API keys or secrets
- Validate all user inputs using Pydantic models
- Use parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection
- Keep dependencies updated and scan for vulnerabilities

### API Design
- Use proper HTTP methods and status codes
- Return consistent JSON response format
- Implement proper error handling and validation
- Use async endpoints for I/O operations

### Error Handling
- Use specific exception types
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Log errors with full context
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes

### Documentation
- Update README.md for any setup changes
- Document all API endpoints
- Include examples in docstrings
- Keep requirements.txt updated

## Development Workflow
Before committing code:
1. Format with Black and isort
2. Lint with flake8
3. Run tests with pytest
4. Check for security issues

## Commit Standards
Use conventional commits:
- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- docs: documentation
- test: tests
- refactor: code refactoring
- chore: maintenance

Examples:
- feat(api): add webhook endpoint for CDR integration
- fix(telegram): resolve bot command parsing issue
- test(api): add unit tests for webhook validation

## File Organization
- API endpoints in api_server.py
- Business logic in separate modules
- Tests in test_*.py files
- Configuration in config.py
- Docker files in root directory

## Performance Guidelines
- Use async/await for I/O operations
- Implement proper database connection pooling
- Use caching where appropriate
- Monitor memory usage and optimize queries

## Security Checklist
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets
- [ ] Input validation implemented
- [ ] SQL injection prevention
- [ ] Dependencies updated
- [ ] Security scanning enabled

## Testing Checklist
- [ ] Unit tests written
- [ ] Error cases tested
- [ ] Edge cases covered
- [ ] Mocks used for external services
- [ ] Test coverage > 80%

## Code Review Checklist
- [ ] Code formatted with Black
- [ ] Imports sorted with isort
- [ ] Linting passes with flake8
- [ ] Tests pass
- [ ] Security scan clean
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Type hints added
- [ ] Error handling implemented
